The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks for deep learning applications, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The focus is on visual recognition tasks, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also proposes novel algorithmic techniques for improving the accuracy and efficiency of SNNs, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses hardware improvements, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
